Aim: Canvasing the Area

HTML5:
   Redesign of HTML with a focus on making more modern features of we browsers easy to work with

   Designed around js and a standardized dom

   Includes built in support for audio and video tags

   Includes element that can be drawn on directly

Canvas:
   HTML5 elemet that provides a drawing area
   
   JS funcs can draw onto a canvas element
   
      Must declare what context you are drawing in (e.g. 2d drawing, 3d drawing, raw bitmap editing
      
      <style>
	#slate{border 1px solid}
      </style
      <canvas width="500" height="300 id="slate"> </canvas> usually leave it empty
      JS:
      var c = document.getElementByID("slate");
      var ctx = c.getContext('2d');
      ctx.fillStyle = "#ff0000";
      ctx.fillRect( 50, 50, 100, 200 )
      ctx.clearRect( 0, 0, 20, 100 )